results.name: Number of pairwise coprime unordered triples of positive integers > 1 summing to n.
comment: The Heinz numbers of these partitions are the intersection of A005408 (no 1's), A014612 (triples), and A302696 (coprime).
link: Fausto A. C. Cariboni, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
example: The a(10) = 1 through a(24) = 15 triples (empty columns indicated by dots, A..J = 10..19):
xref: A055684 is the version for pairs.
A220377 allows 1's, with non-strict version A307719.
A337485 counts these partitions of any length.
A002865 counts partitions with no 1's, with strict case A025147.
A007359 counts pairwise coprime partitions with no 1's.
A078374 counts relatively prime strict partitions.
A200976 and A328673 count pairwise non-coprime partitions.
A302698 counts relatively prime partitions with no 1's.
A305713 counts pairwise coprime strict partitions.
A337452 counts relatively prime strict partitions with no 1's.
